The paper deals with training neural sequence models for grounded dialog generation, which is a problem in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV). The paper proposes a novel training framework that combines generative and discriminative models, which are both common approaches in NLP and CV. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper uses techniques from deep learning (cs.NE), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), which are also likely sub-categories.
